Swashbucklers' Guild Information

Welcome to the swashbucklers' guild.  This is a short list of
commands, GL requirements, SP costs, and other information about
the guild.  To get more complete information on a specific ability,
type 'sbhelp <ability>'.  You can also view the list of guild
emotes by typing 'sbhelp emotes', or the list of skills (without
this preliminary information) by typing 'sbhelp skills'.

There are several other commands you should be aware of.  To
speak on the guild line, use 'sb <text>' or 'esb <text>'.  If
you are GL 15, you can speak on the Blademaster line with
'sbm <text>' and 'esbm <text>'.  You can view the swashbucklers
online with 'swho'.  Finally, you can change your guild title by
typing 'stitle <text>'.

Many of a swashbuckler's attack powers work only with 'blades'.
This includes any knife or dagger, as well as all one-handed
swords, sabres, rapiers, etc.  If you find a weapon which you
think fits this category, but which does not allow use of powers,
please inform your guild coder, or use the bug command to report it.

Most guild powers increase in effect as GL increases.  This is most
evident in the blade styles, but also applies to many other powers
such as sconsider.

Flair is a spendable combat momentum resource. It starts at zero,
builds during combat, and decays outside combat. Critical hits and
wielding a weapon named with 'nameweapon' can generate additional
Flair. Use 'sbhelp flair' for details.

A one-line summary of the various blade styles is available under
'sbhelp styles'.  Information about recent changes to the guild is
available on the guild board and under 'sbhelp new'.

'sbhelp skills' lists the special powers available to swashbucklers,
as well as guild level, SP, and Flair cost requirements. Note that the costs
listed are for neutral swashbucklers. You will find that skills are
cheaper for chaotic swashbucklers and more expensive for lawful ones.
Good and evil have no effect on swashbucklers' skill costs.
